WEBVTT

00:04.435 --> 00:07.108
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

00:07.108 --> 00:10.381
♪ Ooh, ah, ooh ♪

00:10.381 --> 00:13.144
Lilly, you have got to come
horseback riding with me.

00:13.144 --> 00:14.745
It is so much fun.

00:14.745 --> 00:16.117
There's something about
being on a horse

00:16.117 --> 00:18.289
that makes you feel
so happy, so alive...

00:18.289 --> 00:20.391
So not gonna happen.

00:20.391 --> 00:22.223
You don't know
what you're missing.

00:24.495 --> 00:28.599
I think I do,
and it looks like it chafes.

00:28.599 --> 00:31.302
Come on. Riding is
a big part of my life

00:31.302 --> 00:33.234
and I want to share it
with my best friend.

00:33.234 --> 00:35.035
I can't believe
you're afraid
to get on Blue Jeans.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.767
I am not afraid
to get on Blue Jeans.

00:36.767 --> 00:39.310
I'm afraid of
falling off Blue Jeans.

00:39.310 --> 00:43.544
But you skateboard,
snowboard and surf.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.076
What's the difference?

00:45.076 --> 00:48.619
Uh, surfboards don't go
40 miles an hour
and weigh 2,000 pounds.

00:48.619 --> 00:50.581
[horse whinnying]

00:50.581 --> 00:54.725
All right, all right, 1,800,
but the saddle
makes you look hippy.

00:54.725 --> 00:58.229
At least he has hips,
you gutless jellyfish!

00:58.229 --> 01:01.192
Oh, I'm gutless?
Two words for you, missy:

01:01.192 --> 01:03.164
- "Rope climb."
- Ooh.

01:06.737 --> 01:09.270
[all applauding]

01:10.171 --> 01:11.502
Your turn, Miley.

01:11.502 --> 01:13.804
OK. I can do this.

01:13.804 --> 01:15.746
Just gotta take
a running start.

01:16.807 --> 01:19.850
[all chanting] Go! Go! Go!

01:19.850 --> 01:21.182
See ya, suckers!

01:22.813 --> 01:25.816
Yeah, that's right.
The girl can sing The Climb,

01:25.816 --> 01:27.688
she just can't do it.

01:27.688 --> 01:29.220
It's not the same!

01:29.220 --> 01:32.463
That rope is cruel,
pointless torture.

01:32.463 --> 01:34.395
The only thing that is
holding me up there

01:34.395 --> 01:37.498
is the strength of my
very attractive yet
tragically weak hands.

01:37.498 --> 01:39.500
At least the rope
can't suddenly decide,

01:39.500 --> 01:41.572
"Oh, there's
a really low branch.

01:41.572 --> 01:44.405
I think I'll go really fast
and try and get under it."

01:44.405 --> 01:47.708
Come on, look at this face.
He's not gonna hurt you.

01:47.708 --> 01:49.540
"Oh, come on, Lilly.

01:49.540 --> 01:51.612
Riding me's gonna bring
joy and happiness
into your life.

01:51.612 --> 01:53.784
And firmness into those
slightly jiggly thighs."

01:53.784 --> 01:56.287
- [gasps]
- What? He said it, not me.

01:56.287 --> 01:58.349
All right,
I'll make you a deal:

01:58.349 --> 02:00.791
You climb the rope and
I'll ride the stinkin' horse.

02:00.791 --> 02:03.254
- [whinnies]
- No offense, Blue Jeans,

02:03.254 --> 02:05.556
but you do make poopies
on the floor.

02:06.797 --> 02:08.329
OK, fine. Go get changed
and then we'll ride.

02:08.329 --> 02:10.731
Uh, hello.
Why do I have to go first?

02:10.731 --> 02:12.803
Fine. We'll flip a coin.

02:12.803 --> 02:14.835
If it lands on heads,
it's me. Tails, it's you.

02:14.835 --> 02:16.567
- OK.
- Ready?

02:17.208 --> 02:18.369
[coin plopping]

02:18.369 --> 02:20.511
- Ooh...
- Oh...

02:20.511 --> 02:22.313
It's deep in there.

02:22.313 --> 02:24.175
Yeah, but, you know,
I'm pretty sure it's heads.

02:24.175 --> 02:25.176
How do you know?
We'll flip again.

02:25.176 --> 02:27.248
Uh, no, we will not flip it.

02:27.248 --> 02:29.350
- Uh...
- [groans]

02:30.621 --> 02:33.354
Do I really have to do this?

02:33.354 --> 02:35.856
After what I went through
yesterday, oh, yeah.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.730
[Miley] Whoo!

02:39.730 --> 02:41.792
Here we go, everybody!

02:43.163 --> 02:44.635
♪ Come on ♪

02:44.635 --> 02:46.937
♪ You get the limo
out front ♪

02:46.937 --> 02:48.899
♪ Oooh ♪

02:48.899 --> 02:51.942
♪ Hottest styles
Every shoe, every color ♪

02:51.942 --> 02:56.176
♪ Yeah, when you're famous
it can be kind of fun ♪

02:56.176 --> 03:00.751
♪ It's really you
but no one ever discovers ♪

03:00.751 --> 03:04.555
♪ Who would have thought
that a girl like me ♪

03:04.555 --> 03:08.759
♪ Would double
as a superstar ♪

03:08.759 --> 03:10.461
Whooo!

03:10.461 --> 03:14.425
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

03:14.425 --> 03:16.397
♪ Chill it out
Take it slow ♪

03:16.397 --> 03:17.898
♪ Then you rock out the show ♪

03:17.898 --> 03:21.872
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

03:21.872 --> 03:24.775
♪ Mix it all together
and you know ♪

03:24.775 --> 03:27.838
♪ That it's the best
of both worlds ♪♪

03:31.412 --> 03:33.384
♪ Ooh, oh ♪

03:34.745 --> 03:38.589
See the rope, feel the rope,
be the rope.

03:38.589 --> 03:43.694
Or... ditch the rope,
fix the hair, hit the mall.

03:43.694 --> 03:45.726
Oh, no. I am climbing
this bad boy

03:45.726 --> 03:47.398
and you are gettin'
on that horse...

03:47.398 --> 03:50.261
I did it! I did it!

03:50.261 --> 03:52.403
You know this
doesn't count, right?

03:52.403 --> 03:55.536
Oh! I'm a good
four inches higher
than I was an hour ago!

03:55.536 --> 03:59.239
Well, congratulations.
While you descend to base camp,

03:59.239 --> 04:01.512
I'll be home...
not riding Blue Jeans.

04:01.512 --> 04:05.316
Oh, and, uh,
for what it's worth,
hard as a rock.

04:05.316 --> 04:08.849
Wait, no! Don't leave me
here like this!

04:08.849 --> 04:12.423
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

04:14.855 --> 04:17.887
Oh! [moaning]

04:17.887 --> 04:20.961
[smacking lips]

04:20.961 --> 04:25.466
Son, you know, one of these days
Siena's parents are gonna want
to share a meal with you.

04:25.466 --> 04:28.399
[belches loudly]

04:28.399 --> 04:31.642
When that day comes,
I suggest you don't
make it breakfast.

04:31.642 --> 04:35.546
For your information, Dad,
Siena likes me
just the way that I am.

04:35.546 --> 04:37.708
- [doorbell rings]
- [Siena] Knock, knock, knock.

04:38.509 --> 04:40.280
[exhales] Whoa!

04:40.280 --> 04:42.383
[sniffs] Yow!

04:45.716 --> 04:47.918
[exclaiming] Ow!

04:53.864 --> 04:56.467
Well, that oughta
give it some tang.

05:00.971 --> 05:03.634
[wincing] Good morning,
my lovely.

05:03.634 --> 05:08.409
Oh, are you ever
not adorable?

05:08.409 --> 05:11.612
Depends on if you like
spit in your lemonade.

05:11.612 --> 05:15.886
I, uh... thought
you had a photo shoot.

05:15.886 --> 05:18.589
OK, that's kinda
getting old now.
Can we move on?

05:18.589 --> 05:20.521
I'm trying.

05:20.521 --> 05:21.852
So I've gotta get
to the shoot.

05:21.852 --> 05:23.924
But here's that book
I told you about.

05:23.924 --> 05:26.727
And I can't wait
to read it!

05:26.727 --> 05:29.500
Seriously,
enough with the voice.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.605
[wincing] OK, bye.

05:39.910 --> 05:41.512
[gargling]

05:46.116 --> 05:47.648
Whoo, doggies!

05:47.648 --> 05:49.680
To Kill A Mockingbird?

05:49.680 --> 05:52.483
Now, son,
that's a real book
right there, now.

05:52.483 --> 05:55.656
Hundreds of pages,
no pictures.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.528
Dad, really...

05:57.528 --> 05:58.959
No pictures?

05:58.959 --> 06:02.633
You know what?
It doesn't matter. That's fine.

06:02.633 --> 06:04.995
This is my girlfriend's
favorite book and if
she wants me to read it,

06:04.995 --> 06:08.669
then read it I shall...
with the eyes of love.

06:11.602 --> 06:13.874
Aaaaand begin.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.076
[snoring]

06:17.748 --> 06:22.112
♪ Ah, ah, ooh, ah, ooh ♪

06:22.112 --> 06:23.714
Miley,
give it up, all right?

06:23.714 --> 06:26.086
You're never gonna climb
the rope and I'm never
gonna ride the horse.

06:26.086 --> 06:28.719
Tragic, but somehow
I'll survive.

06:28.719 --> 06:30.721
Oh, no. No, no, no.

06:30.721 --> 06:33.824
You're gonna know
the joy of riding if I have
to climb 100 ropes...

06:33.824 --> 06:36.066
Which I don't,
'cause our deal was one.

06:37.668 --> 06:39.700
Hey, Lilly, when did
Oliver get back?

06:39.700 --> 06:42.673
What are you talking about?
He's still on tour.

06:42.673 --> 06:45.405
Then who's
the shaggy-haired
pasty-faced guy

06:45.405 --> 06:47.608
who just slammed
his finger in a locker
and screamed like a girl?

06:47.608 --> 06:48.739
[gasping] Ollie-pop!

06:49.910 --> 06:51.712
[Miley]
Lilly, come back, look!

06:54.144 --> 06:56.647
I did it! I did it!

06:56.647 --> 06:59.089
But you were...
And I was...

06:59.089 --> 07:00.651
And now you're...

07:00.651 --> 07:02.693
What are you, a vampire?

07:02.693 --> 07:04.825
Hey, life
is full of surprises.

07:04.825 --> 07:09.159
I'm at the top of the rope,
and your girlie man-friend
is out in the hallway.

07:09.159 --> 07:10.931
Ollie-pop!

07:10.931 --> 07:13.964
Wow, my first lie.
What a rush!

07:13.964 --> 07:15.706
I have to try that again.

07:15.706 --> 07:18.809
Hey, Ms. Kunkle, nice shoes!

07:18.809 --> 07:21.441
They're really not!

07:21.441 --> 07:23.043
OK, boys, lemme down.

07:23.043 --> 07:25.816
Make it quick before
Lilly finds out it's
really just Emo Ernie

07:25.816 --> 07:28.448
in a pair of skinny jeans,
you know what I'm saying?

07:28.448 --> 07:29.650
[exclaims]

07:30.851 --> 07:33.484
Little too fast!

07:33.484 --> 07:36.727
♪ Hey, yeah, hey, yeah ♪

07:38.489 --> 07:42.092
Wow! Talk about
your page-turner.

07:45.896 --> 07:47.067
Little help here!

07:48.699 --> 07:50.771
Uh, sorry, Dad.

07:50.771 --> 07:54.074
Lost in the fascinating world
that is To Kill a...
Dribgnikcom!

07:55.075 --> 07:57.177
Uh, Mockingbird!

07:57.177 --> 08:01.552
Dribgnikcom was the original
title, in honor of the author's
Swedish grandmother...

08:01.552 --> 08:03.754
[Swedish accent]
Inga Dribgnikcom.

08:03.754 --> 08:07.818
Really?. I loved that book
but I don't remember that part.

08:07.818 --> 08:11.892
Well, I guess I just care
a little bit more about
classic works of literature.

08:11.892 --> 08:16.066
Now if you'll excuse me,
I don't wanna lose
my mockingbird mojo.

08:16.066 --> 08:18.829
Or, as we say like
in Swedish...

08:18.829 --> 08:22.072
[Swedish accent]
Dribgnikcom ojom,
by Yiminy... Cricket.

08:23.774 --> 08:26.837
So what'd you think
of the way the author
introduced Jem's broken arm?

08:26.837 --> 08:30.180
Shh! Dad, don't spoil it.
I haven't got there yet.

08:30.180 --> 08:33.013
It's the first sentence
of the book.

08:33.013 --> 08:35.885
If you don't count
the title page,

08:35.885 --> 08:39.690
which I found so riveting,
I've read 71 times.

08:39.690 --> 08:42.192
Two days and that's
as far as you got?

08:43.654 --> 08:45.826
It's just so thick!

08:45.826 --> 08:49.529
And there are so many words
and they're all... different!

08:50.661 --> 08:52.763
Dad, I'm part of
the video game generation.

08:52.763 --> 08:56.066
I can't handle long and slow,
I need short and fast!

08:56.066 --> 08:58.739
Son, if you don't
finish that book,
your relationship

08:58.739 --> 09:01.742
with your b-b-bikini model's
gonna be short and fast.

09:01.742 --> 09:03.914
Come on, son,
think about it.

09:03.914 --> 09:07.047
The brain's a muscle.
You gotta exercise it.

09:07.047 --> 09:10.280
You dig into a classic
like To Kill A Mockingbird,

09:10.280 --> 09:13.123
before you know it, your eyes
are gonna be glued to the...

09:13.123 --> 09:14.825
[snoring]

09:16.126 --> 09:18.759
...inside of your eyelids.

09:20.731 --> 09:23.764
One day, you're gonna
make me proud, son...

09:23.764 --> 09:26.296
Just hope I can survive
all those other days.

09:30.871 --> 09:32.843
Brain is a muscle, right?

09:32.843 --> 09:35.305
Dad? Dad?

09:36.747 --> 09:40.210
OK, now where was I?

09:44.284 --> 09:47.057
Well, at least
I'm reading...

09:48.719 --> 09:51.792
...if you count
"Grrrrr" as a word.

09:51.792 --> 09:53.764
And I do.

09:54.865 --> 09:58.128
What are you looking at me for,
you troglodyte!

09:58.128 --> 09:59.770
Troglo-what?

09:59.770 --> 10:02.232
Look it up!

10:05.676 --> 10:07.307
Wow, that was weird!

10:12.843 --> 10:17.347
You're gonna read that book
and you're gonna read it now!

10:17.347 --> 10:19.850
But reading hurts.

10:19.850 --> 10:21.051
Not as much as this!

10:22.092 --> 10:24.925
- [grunts]
- [exclaims]

10:26.356 --> 10:30.901
You see,
reading is a joy!

10:30.901 --> 10:32.663
[yelling] Ow!

10:37.968 --> 10:42.042
Reading takes you to new
and exciting places!

10:46.917 --> 10:48.749
[whimpering] Daddy!

10:48.749 --> 10:50.851
You can't see me!

10:50.851 --> 10:52.823
- [shrieking]
- [yelling]

10:52.823 --> 10:54.384
- [thump]
- [exclaims]

10:58.028 --> 11:00.761
I gotta start reading.

11:02.933 --> 11:04.264
But first a sandwich.

11:05.295 --> 11:08.969
♪ Yeah, yeah, ooh ♪

11:08.969 --> 11:11.702
Come on, stop looking
at me like that.

11:11.702 --> 11:14.705
I only lied so Lilly could know
the joy of riding a horse.

11:14.705 --> 11:17.147
And so I could be right.
But that stays between us.

11:17.147 --> 11:19.079
Shh...

11:22.913 --> 11:24.955
I'm ready!

11:24.955 --> 11:27.357
For what?
Shipping yourself off
to Wimpy World?

11:27.357 --> 11:29.459
Hey, sounds fun!
Let's go there instead!

11:29.459 --> 11:33.323
Uh-uh-uh! Your bubble-wrapped
butt ain't goin' nowhere.
Come on.

11:33.323 --> 11:36.466
- No, Miley, please!
- Oh, come on!

11:36.466 --> 11:38.869
If you didn't wanna go riding,
why'd you put on that outfit?

11:38.869 --> 11:41.101
'Cause I look cute in it.

11:41.101 --> 11:44.905
Lilly, you promised
you'd ride the horse
if I climbed the rope.

11:44.905 --> 11:46.937
And I sucked it up
and I climbed that rope.

11:46.937 --> 11:48.939
[horse nickers]

11:50.110 --> 11:52.112
OK, you're right.
I'll do it.

11:52.112 --> 11:53.914
- OK.
- OK.

11:53.914 --> 11:56.346
It's easy. All you
have to do is hang on.

11:57.317 --> 11:59.249
To the horse!

11:59.249 --> 12:00.951
- Oh, right. OK.
- OK, ready?

12:00.951 --> 12:03.954
- [grunting]
- One, two, three.

12:06.827 --> 12:08.028
Am I on?

12:08.028 --> 12:10.260
Open your eyes
and find out.

12:13.063 --> 12:15.365
I'm on a horse!
[gasping] I'm on a horse!

12:15.365 --> 12:16.937
[nervous] I'm on a horse!

12:16.937 --> 12:18.368
It's OK, just hold on.

12:18.368 --> 12:19.770
I'll take you down
to the barn,

12:19.770 --> 12:20.971
we'll get Dad's horse
and we'll go for a ride.

12:20.971 --> 12:22.372
Not so fast! Not so fast!

12:22.372 --> 12:24.744
We're not moving yet.

12:24.744 --> 12:27.447
- Right.
- Now we're moving.

12:27.447 --> 12:29.479
[gasping] Not so fast!
Not so fast!

12:31.351 --> 12:34.524
Look at me, look at me,
I'm doing it, I'm doing it!

12:34.524 --> 12:36.356
Oh, my gosh!

12:36.356 --> 12:39.259
Yeah, riding with you,
not as much fun
as I pictured it.

12:39.259 --> 12:40.530
Hey, I'm going
faster than you!

12:40.530 --> 12:42.332
- Hey...
- I'm going faster than you!

12:44.034 --> 12:46.967
Why didn't you tell me
how fun this was!

12:46.967 --> 12:48.939
- What was I thinking?
- Come on...

12:48.939 --> 12:52.072
- [horse whinnies]
- Whoa, whoa whoa whoa!

12:53.243 --> 12:54.274
[Lilly hits ground]

12:54.274 --> 12:57.077
- Lilly!
- [groaning]

12:58.078 --> 13:00.150
- Are you OK?
- No, my leg!

13:00.150 --> 13:02.012
Daddy!

13:02.012 --> 13:04.184
[whinnying]

13:04.184 --> 13:05.986
Dad!

13:10.420 --> 13:14.364
♪ Ooh, whoa, ooh ♪

13:14.364 --> 13:16.466
Don't worry, I'll take
such good care of you,

13:16.466 --> 13:17.968
you won't even know
your leg's broken.

13:17.968 --> 13:19.329
- Ow!
- Ooh...

13:19.329 --> 13:20.430
Starting now!

13:20.430 --> 13:24.204
- Sorry, hold on.
- Ow!

13:24.204 --> 13:26.276
[grunting]

13:27.237 --> 13:29.339
- [exclaims]
- I meant now.

13:29.339 --> 13:31.942
Sorry, sorry,
I meant now.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.415
Mile, I'm sure glad
you can sing,

13:35.415 --> 13:37.487
'cause you sure don't have
a future in nursing.

13:37.487 --> 13:40.020
[phone beeps]

13:40.020 --> 13:42.152
Oh... Great news.

13:42.152 --> 13:45.295
Jackson found Blue Jeans
and they're on
their way here now.

13:45.295 --> 13:47.858
Oh, that's great.
I was really worried.

13:47.858 --> 13:49.329
You don't think it was
anything I did, right?

13:49.329 --> 13:52.132
Heck no, honey, anything
could've spooked him.

13:52.132 --> 13:54.464
A flock of birds, a shadow
in the bushes, anything...

13:54.464 --> 13:57.938
Yeah. I'm just really
sorry this happened.

13:57.938 --> 14:01.341
Don't be. You were right.
Riding Blue Jeans was fun.

14:01.341 --> 14:03.143
And besides,
we made a deal.

14:03.143 --> 14:05.615
I said I would ride the horse
if you climbed the rope.

14:05.615 --> 14:09.079
And you climbed the rope
and I know how hard
that was for you.

14:09.079 --> 14:11.081
Yep...

14:12.182 --> 14:14.885
That's right.
I climbed the rope.

14:14.885 --> 14:17.527
Clearly I climbed the rope,
'cause you saw me up there.

14:17.527 --> 14:19.529
It's not like I didn't
climb the rope,

14:19.529 --> 14:23.433
because how else would
I have gotten up there?
[nervous laugh]

14:23.433 --> 14:27.597
It's not like
I lied about the rope
to get you on the horse.

14:27.597 --> 14:29.299
Miley?

14:29.299 --> 14:31.241
I lied about the rope
to get you on the horse.

14:31.241 --> 14:33.303
- You what?!
- OK, look, I'm really sorry.

14:33.303 --> 14:36.206
I know it was wrong,
but I knew you'd like
riding Blue Jeans.

14:36.206 --> 14:39.179
And you did,
up until the whole
little boo-boo part.

14:39.179 --> 14:40.880
Come here,
I'll boo-boo you!

14:40.880 --> 14:45.385
OK, look, I know I lied,
but I did it with love.

14:45.385 --> 14:47.487
All right,
you're gonna have to
come down eventually.

14:47.487 --> 14:49.519
And when you
do, I'll be here...

14:49.519 --> 14:51.291
[whispering] ...waiting!

14:52.462 --> 14:54.464
Dad? Dad...

14:54.464 --> 14:57.497
I got Blue Jeans
back in the barn,
but he's kinda limping.

14:57.497 --> 14:58.628
- What?
- What?

14:58.628 --> 15:00.300
I'll call the vet.

15:03.173 --> 15:05.475
- Is he gonna be OK?
- It was a snake bite.

15:05.475 --> 15:07.577
He must've gotten it
after he ran off.

15:07.577 --> 15:09.339
But I was able
to treat it in time,

15:09.339 --> 15:11.211
and Blue Jeans
is gonna be just fine.

15:11.211 --> 15:12.512
- Oh, good.
- Great news.

15:12.512 --> 15:14.144
So, what's gonna happen now?

15:14.144 --> 15:15.515
Well, the leg's
still really sore,

15:15.515 --> 15:17.547
so he's reluctant
to put any weight on it.

15:17.547 --> 15:19.019
but once he does,
he's gonna be fine.

15:19.019 --> 15:21.191
Would it help
if we nagged him a little?

15:23.223 --> 15:25.495
Get it? "Nag?"

15:25.495 --> 15:28.498
- [all] 'Cause he's a horse.
- Got it.

15:28.498 --> 15:31.431
Or you could go back in there,
tell him that joke,

15:31.431 --> 15:33.033
and he may just
run for the hills again.

15:33.033 --> 15:36.006
Burned!
Up high, doc!

15:36.006 --> 15:38.238
But you should know,
earlier today, this hand

15:38.238 --> 15:39.569
pulled a calf
out of a mama cow.

15:39.569 --> 15:41.541
You're really enjoying this,
aren't you?

15:41.541 --> 15:44.544
Yep. When you're a vet,
you live for these moments.

15:44.544 --> 15:48.118
Just try to get him
back up on his feet,
I'll check back in later.

15:48.118 --> 15:49.119
- OK?
- Thank you.

15:49.119 --> 15:50.520
Thanks, Doc.

15:50.520 --> 15:52.482
Hey, you work
with animals.

15:52.482 --> 15:55.355
- Ever read
 To Kill A Mockingbird?
 - Of course. I loved it.

15:55.355 --> 15:58.488
Think you could sum it up
in the time it takes
to walk to your car?

15:58.488 --> 16:00.690
You can skip
the title page, I got that.

16:00.690 --> 16:04.064
You do know it's not about
an actual bird, right?

16:04.064 --> 16:05.565
Duh!

16:05.565 --> 16:09.069
Not about a bird...

16:12.502 --> 16:14.674
Come on, Blue Jeans.
You heard Dr. Yamada.

16:14.674 --> 16:17.447
Everything's fine,
all you gotta do is stand up.

16:17.447 --> 16:20.350
So, here we go,
let's go, HNO!

16:20.350 --> 16:23.613
Get it?
"Horse's night out?"

16:23.613 --> 16:25.755
Oh, no, Dad,
I'm turning into you.

16:27.587 --> 16:30.160
Huh? Huh?

16:30.160 --> 16:32.592
You know you wanna share
a hay bale with this one.

16:33.693 --> 16:36.196
Her name is Suzanne!

16:36.196 --> 16:41.231
She likes carrots, apples
and long walks on the
horse-approved beaches!

16:43.033 --> 16:45.705
Nothing?
It's the bonnet, isn't it?

16:45.705 --> 16:48.338
I told you it made
your nose look big!

16:50.009 --> 16:52.642
Come on, buddy,
it's just a sore leg.

16:52.642 --> 16:55.085
Nothing to be afraid of.

16:55.085 --> 16:56.586
Lilly, get out
of your wheel chair.

16:56.586 --> 16:58.418
- Huh?
- Get out of your wheelchair.

16:58.418 --> 16:59.719
Show him you're not
afraid to stand up.

16:59.719 --> 17:01.551
But I am afraid
to stand up.

17:01.551 --> 17:03.153
Do not say that
in front of the horse.

17:03.153 --> 17:04.694
And smile, you're gonna
scare Blue Jeans.

17:04.694 --> 17:06.326
Why don't I just do
a little dance?

17:06.326 --> 17:08.627
- That'd be awesome!
- No, it would be sarcasm.

17:08.627 --> 17:11.431
Come on, how long are you
gonna keep milkin'
that broken leg bit?

17:11.431 --> 17:13.502
Oh, I don't know,

17:13.502 --> 17:17.166
I was thinking just
up to the time my leg
isn't broken anymore!

17:19.108 --> 17:20.609
Dad, call the vet!

17:20.609 --> 17:23.613
♪ Ooh, ah, ooh, ah ♪

17:27.117 --> 17:28.578
So when's the vet
gonna be here?

17:28.578 --> 17:30.350
She'll be here
as soon as she can.

17:30.350 --> 17:32.582
I don't get it.
She said Blue Jeans
was gonna be fine.

17:32.582 --> 17:35.125
Lilly, it's not
the snake bite.
It's just...

17:35.125 --> 17:37.587
It's not good for a horse
to lie down for too long.

17:37.587 --> 17:40.590
Blue Jeans should've stood up
by now. But he's hasn't.

17:42.132 --> 17:44.334
Sometimes when an old horse
won't get up,

17:44.334 --> 17:46.766
it means they've decided
it's their time.

18:07.817 --> 18:10.089
Remember back when
you was a little girl,

18:10.089 --> 18:13.823
we went down to the corral
to pick out your
very first horse?

18:15.465 --> 18:16.766
Yeah, I was four.

18:16.766 --> 18:19.699
You put me on your shoulders
so I could see better.

18:19.699 --> 18:22.632
There were some beauties
out there that day,

18:22.632 --> 18:26.336
but you kept pointing
to the little scrawny
white one in the corner.

18:26.336 --> 18:28.578
I wanted you to get
the big chestnut mare,

18:28.578 --> 18:30.280
but before I knew it,
he was...

18:30.280 --> 18:32.612
- Tugging on my blue jeans.
- Yeah.

18:32.612 --> 18:34.544
And peein' on my boots.

18:34.544 --> 18:36.416
That's when I knew
he was the one for me.

18:38.548 --> 18:40.750
I'm not ready
to let go, Dad.

18:42.422 --> 18:44.394
I'm hoping
you don't have to.

18:45.725 --> 18:48.458
But right now,
all we can do is pray.

18:55.465 --> 18:58.468
♪ There's a gold frame ♪

18:58.468 --> 19:00.710
♪ That sits by the window ♪

19:00.710 --> 19:03.773
♪ And my heart breaks ♪

19:03.773 --> 19:08.848
♪ A little more
each time I try ♪

19:08.848 --> 19:14.254
♪ To picture
the memory inside ♪

19:16.686 --> 19:19.329
♪ There's a notebook ♪

19:19.329 --> 19:21.791
♪ It's too hard to read it ♪

19:21.791 --> 19:24.864
♪ But if you look ♪

19:24.864 --> 19:29.869
♪ You'd see how you look
through my eyes ♪

19:29.869 --> 19:34.704
♪ But now one more
chapter's gone by ♪

19:34.704 --> 19:38.448
♪ And I know ♪

19:38.448 --> 19:43.653
♪ It's time to move on
even though I'm not ready ♪

19:43.653 --> 19:46.386
♪ I've got to be strong ♪

19:46.386 --> 19:48.858
♪ And trust
where you're heading ♪

19:48.858 --> 19:51.261
♪ And even though
it's not easy ♪

19:51.261 --> 19:52.922
♪ It's not easy ♪

19:52.922 --> 19:58.298
♪ I know the right
kind of love ♪

19:58.298 --> 20:01.901
♪ Doesn't wanna
miss the future ♪

20:01.901 --> 20:04.534
♪ By staying in the past ♪

20:04.534 --> 20:07.377
♪ It will always hold on ♪

20:07.377 --> 20:09.709
♪ But never hold you back ♪

20:09.709 --> 20:12.382
♪ And even though
it's not easy ♪

20:12.382 --> 20:14.244
♪ It's not easy ♪

20:14.244 --> 20:18.848
♪ Right now
the right kind of love ♪

20:18.848 --> 20:24.924
♪ Is a love that lets go ♪

20:32.302 --> 20:35.004
♪ It's time I love you ♪

20:35.004 --> 20:40.910
♪ With a love
that lets go ♪♪

20:42.772 --> 20:46.576
Mile... Mile...

20:47.817 --> 20:49.819
Is he gone?

20:49.819 --> 20:51.851
Why don't you ask him
for yourself?

20:51.851 --> 20:53.623
Blue Jeans!

20:53.623 --> 20:56.786
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

20:58.858 --> 21:01.431
[Miley] Dedicated to my
real-life horse, Roam-Man.

21:01.431 --> 21:03.262
Happy trails to you, buddy.

21:07.437 --> 21:08.798
So what did you think?

21:08.798 --> 21:12.642
- This book? Wow!
- Mm-hmm.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.276
I can't even
put it into words.

21:17.276 --> 21:19.579
I mean, the author's words,
those are words.

21:19.579 --> 21:22.752
But my words,
to describe those words?

21:22.752 --> 21:26.356
I have no words for that.

21:26.356 --> 21:29.819
- You didn't read the book.
- No.

21:29.819 --> 21:32.622
- I tried, but...
- There were so many words

21:32.622 --> 21:34.924
and every time
you turned a page
there were more?

21:34.924 --> 21:38.468
I wanted
to tell you, but...

21:38.468 --> 21:40.670
I was afraid you'd be
disappointed in me.

21:45.335 --> 21:48.007
I'm not disappointed.

21:48.007 --> 21:50.680
- You're not?
- No.

21:50.680 --> 21:54.584
- Because you are
gonna read the book.
- I am?

21:54.584 --> 21:58.648
If you wanna keep dating
a b-b-b-bikini model, you are.

22:02.522 --> 22:04.954
Dad, I'm gonna need
coffee and lots of it!

22:09.699 --> 22:14.364
Hmm. Jackson overcame his fear
in telling Siena the truth.

22:14.364 --> 22:16.706
I got over my fear
in riding a horse.

22:16.706 --> 22:18.838
And Blue Jeans conquered
his fear and stood up.

22:18.838 --> 22:22.472
Well, who do we know who still
hasn't faced their fear?

22:22.472 --> 22:25.745
- Who?
- [groans]

22:26.716 --> 22:28.578
I did it! I did it!

22:28.578 --> 22:29.749
I did it
when I was four.

22:29.749 --> 22:30.780
(mocking) I did it
when I was four.

22:30.780 --> 22:32.782
[mocking]

22:32.782 --> 22:34.854
Show-off.
